: 184 (cat.). syn. n.

This species has been reported from central and southeastern China, Japan, Taiwan, and Australia, India, and the Indo-Pacific Region (Caroline Islands, Childers Island, Cook Islands, Fiji, Gilbert Island, Indonesia, Mariana Islands, Marshall Islands, New Caledonia, New Hebrides, Papua New Guinea, Philippine Islands, Pitcairn Island, Rapa Island, Ryuku Islands, Samoa, Society Islands, Solomon Islands, South Korea, Swain Islands, and Tonga Islands) ( Schuh 1984 , 1995; Kerzhner and Josifov 1995; Cassis and Gross 1995 ). Based on specimens in the USNM, most or all records reported by Schuh (1984) from India and Sri Lanka should be applied to Tytthus parviceps ;
Schuh's (1984)
record from Hawaii is based on two specimens intercepted on international commerce at Honolulu (without origin indi cated ).
